and his knight is untouchable.}) 16. a3 $5 {Controlling an important square
from which Black can conduct their counterplay.} (16. Bg5 $5) 16... c5 17. Nb3
{[%csl Rd7][%cal Ge4e5,Gd2d7]} Be6 18. Na5 {[%cal Ga5c6] The knight creates
threats and can always return toward the center with Na5-Nc4.} Rb6 19. e5 Nd7
20. Qf4 $14 {[%cal Gb2b3,Ga5c4,Gh6g5] The position is complex but White has a
nice plus. Conclusion: The line with 3...g6 is not very popular. The character
of the positions is sharp in nature and with opposing attacks. In most lines,
White has a comfortable advantage, however, the line with 8...Re8 followed by
9...d5 shouldn't be underestimated.} *

