gxf5 $14 {With a small advantage for White in a complex position.}) 14. g4 b5
15. Nf5 Bxf5 16. gxf5 b4 (16... c6 17. Ne2 a5 18. Rg1 $16 {[%csl Rg7][%cal
Gg1g7] With considerable pressure on the g-file.}) 17. Bxf6 $1 Bxf6 18. Nd5 $16
{White has a magnificent knight and weaknesses to target. Potkin,V (2574)
-Ivanov,A (2400)/Sochi RUS 2017 (41) 1-0 Conclusion: This transposition to the
Ruy Lopez will be liked by whoever has the Steinitz Defense in their
repertoire with the Black pieces. It's a solid variation but somewhat passive
for Black. White, with simple moves, gets good opportunities to get a good
position, both strategic with a space advantage or dynamic with an attack with
opposite castling.} *

