e3 to the f5-square. White's main plan is the f2-f4 break, but he must do it
carefully, improving his pieces without haste. As long as this break isn't
played (f2-f4), Black has difficulties organizing his counterplay.} Rf8 16. Nc4
b6 17. g3 $1 {Little by little, White is building his game on the kingside.}
