$18) (14... Qd7 15. Nd5 Nf6 16. Nf5 $18 {Black's position collapses.}) (14...
f6 {This is too passive and White simply continues the attack.} 15. Qg4 $1 $18
{[%cal Gh4f5,Gc3d5]}) 15. Nf5 $1 {[%cal Gc3d5]} Rg6 (15... Qd7 $2 16. Nd5 Rg6
17. Nfe7+ $1 $18 {[%csl Rf7][%cal Gf3f7]}) (15... Ne7 $4 16. Nxe7+ Qxe7 17. Nd5
$18) 16. Nd5 Nf6 17. Nh4 $1 Rg5 18. Nxf6+ $18 {These variations are another
example of White's potential on the kingside.}) 14... Ne7 (14... Rf6 $6 15. Nf5
$1 {[%cal Ga1f1,Gc3d5] And White continues to make progress.}) 15. Raf1 {
[%csl Rf7][%cal Gf3f7]} Ng6 $8 (15... f6 $2 16. Qg4 Qd7 17. Rxf6 $18) 16. Nf5
$1 c6 $5 {[%cal Rc3d5]} (16... Nf6 $2 17. Nd5 $1 $18 ({Equally good is:} 17.
