{[%evp 0,11,36,34,54,64,77,62,71,59,91,42,49,48]} {How should White make
progress positionally?} 19. Ne3 $1 {White shouldn't rush with the f2-f4 pawn
break but should rather prepare it patiently. The knight is on an excellent
square from where it can jump to f5 at the right moment.} (19. f4 $2 {Is too
premature.} exf4 20. gxf4 ({The lesser evil is:} 20. Bxf4 $13 {and there is no
sign of an advantage for White.}) 20... Rae8 21. Qd3 Nh4 $1 22. Bh1 Bf5 $1 $17
{A good counterplay by Black, demonstrating the dangers of rushing with the
f2-f4 pawn break.}) 19... Nh7 20. c4 $1 {Fixing Black's pawns on the queenside
and making the a4-a5 pawn break possible.} Rae8 {White has two promising
continuations that reflect his advantage.} 21. Qh5 {[%cal Rf7f5]} (21. a5 $16 {
White takes advantage and plays on both flanks.}) 21... Nf6 22. Qf3 {[%cal
Ge3f5]} Bc8 23. Nf5 Bxf5 24. Qxf5 $16 {[%cal Ga4a5] White is playing all over
the board and has a slight but very pleasant advantage.} *

