{[%evp 0,13,28,8,8,0,0,0,0,0,0,75,159,159,159,128]} {What is the precise
sequence of moves to fight for the advantage?} 1. f4 $1 exf3 2. Nxf7 $1 {
This unexpected sacrifice gives rise to great tactical complications.} Qe7 $2 (
2... Kxf7 $2 3. Bb3+ Be6 4. Qxf3+ $18) ({The best answer for Black is the very
difficult to find:} 2... Qf6 $1 3. Rxf3 Bg4 {A fundamental complement of 2...
Qf6.} 4. Rxf6 Bxd1 5. Rxd1 gxf6 6. Nh6+ Kh8 7. Bc1 $14 {White's position is
slightly preferable and easier to play.}) 3. Rxf3 $1 ({A serious error is:} 3.
Qxf3 $4 Qxe3+ 4. Qxe3 Rxe3 5. Ng5 h6 $1 $19 {Black defends from White's
threats and keeps the extra piece.}) 3... Bg4 4. Bg5 Bxf3 (4... Qd7 5. Bb3 Be6
